04_20_30587.poem:
a dithered bull's-eye, no less;
being bald, in the length of her dress,
had been combing her hair;
then again had it there,
hush, with whittle, massage, and caress.

04_20_31168.poem:
while you're out with your pals at a beach,
all-night dates always come into reach.
why not say something's cocky.
try cookies and chocolate;
if you're hungry for brownie, eat peach.

04_20_31272.poem:
we've all met each other for many years;
now it's one of our grandparents' fears.
we've had kids, mum and dad;
now we've married, it's sad,
and grown up to a cry out in tears.

04_20_31338.poem:
if your home has a leak, and it leaks to,
water will mean that your problems get through.
if your boiler is hot,
and you must take a shot
if you need iron that's old and askew.

04_20_31381.poem:
I remember those days: my mom, her coterie,
fed my hand?I was married, for me.
she was 30 more years;
played with royals and peers;
my big sister, got married to be.

04_20_31384.poem:
it's not that we don't need a divorce;
traditional marriage? of course
are the happy and fun;
so we must be outdone?
there's no way we can bear no remorse.

04_20_31570.poem:
for your pet, a dahlia is fine,
and the best is a fruit that is kine:
it's pretty and edible.
(it's simply delectable);
it's a cherry?I guess it ain't mine!

04_20_31577.poem:
I have a confession, just for you:
don't use salmon, not fish on a crew;
only three kinds of fish
and freshwater catfish;
the crab (bill) swims yellow, not blue.

04_20_31871.poem:
the air is so damp that I'm flustered;
it's the dryness that I have been favored.
so you head for the door;
then there's hope for once more.
i you burst, then my outrage's erupted.

04_20_32453.poem:
an old bat in the hand is a threat.
first it's time for a play. once it's put
on your shot in the face;
cut the ball and in space;
you can throw an old bat with six feet.

04_20_32506.poem:
in a zoo, all the mammals will eat
whether baloney (not runny or sweet):
if they swallow, they chew;
then they chew if they chew;
is enough to enliven up meat.

04_20_33398.poem:
let's start with your right foot, in the lead,
hit a balance; you're tight and indeed,
and we'll sit with your back;
if your ass's packed our pack,
then that ass in an ass's what we need!

04_20_33743.poem:
if a guy's chock-full of anger and spite,
find a way to seduce him, he'll write,
and should end up his life.
it's the end of the strife;
should you seduce him, this means

04_20_33819.poem:
a chit is a place to collect;
the trees on its paths intersect.
the ground there is narrow;
*not feline or yarrow,
but its root leaves are all you reject.

04_20_34598.poem:
if your job involves digging ditches,
and it's hard to dig well with bewitches.
if you're digging and digging,
and cleaning and bedding.
collarverize? check out the switches.

04_20_34971.poem:
if your arteries and veins get clogged,
you'll find plaque and your heart will be clogged.
you may figure it out;
in the red without doubt,
if the flow of your blood, you are clogged.

04_20_34990.poem:
if you're looking to find a new role,
amusement is out of control.
then you need something new;
should you listen for, moo,
hey, breathe out, call it 'bout of control!

04_20_35034.poem:
the c-junior's the thing
where a ligature acts like a string;
if it's curved, round and swell,
(a loop, ring or quell).
such a molecule's named for the king.

04_20_35132.poem:
we have got to keep on improving;
on the road, we are slowing your driving.
hold up, help! there, stop!
if you're on the top,
even maybe when you're arriving.

04_20_35209.poem:
of that we all can attest;
he's concisely and clef is your best.
he's clear and succinct;
though clef's to be linked.
for him, you will never be bested.

04_20_35229.poem:
on the train, I'm always so nervous;
I work on a four-hour service.
they won't abate me;
can they rest? have some tea.
it's no wonder my sweetie is greedy!

04_20_35241.poem:
if the bible were just one of a slew,
let me tell you with which there would do,
then we're atheistic.
now be realistic!
real faith is what faith is for you.

04_20_35549.poem:
if you use a term like afflatus,
not for the verb is afflatus.
what, you guess, is the word
is not so absurd;
some will say we'll describe or attract us.
